python
# L√™ a quantidade de matrizes
n = int(input())
matrices = []

# L√™ cada matriz e transforma os valores em inteiros

    matrix = input()
    matrices.append(list(map(int, matrix.split(','))))

# Fun√ß√£o para calcular acur√°cia
def calcular_acuracia(tp, fp, fn, tn):
    total = tp + fp + fn + tn
    if total == 0:
        return 0
    return (tp + tn) / total

# Fun√ß√£o para calcular precis√£o
def calcular_precisao(tp, fp):
    if (tp + fp) == 0:
        return 0
    return tp / (tp + fp)

# Fun√ß√£o para encontrar a melhor matriz
def best_performance(matrices):
    best_index = 0
    best_accuracy = 0
    best_precision = 0

    for index, matrix in enumerate(matrices):
        tp, fp, fn, tn = matrix
        acc = calcular_acuracia(tp, fp, fn, tn)
        prec = calcular_precisao(tp, fp)

        # Atualiza se encontrar uma matriz com melhor desempenho
        if (acc > best_accuracy) or (acc == best_accuracy and prec > best_precision):
            best_index = index
            best_accuracy = acc
            best_precision = prec

    return best_index, best_accuracy, best_precision

# Chamada da fun√ß√£o
